@page "/security"

<section class="page-hero bg-light py-5">
    <div class="container">
        <h1 class="display-5 fw-bold">Security and trust</h1>
        <p class="lead">ApiTester is designed to protect API data with layered controls, transparent audits, and enterprise-ready governance.</p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="py-5">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row g-4">
            <div class="col-lg-6">
                <h2 class="h4 fw-bold">Platform safeguards</h2>
                <p>We combine encryption, least-privilege access, and continuous monitoring to keep your environments secure.</p>
                <ul class="list-unstyled">
                    <li class="mb-2">Encryption at rest and in transit with rotating keys.</li>
                    <li class="mb-2">Audit trails for test runs, deployments, and configuration changes.</li>
                    <li class="mb-2">IP allowlists, SSO, and MFA for privileged users.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-6">
                <h2 class="h4 fw-bold">SSRF protections</h2>
                <p>We block server-side request forgery by constraining outbound calls to approved targets, validating DNS resolution, and rejecting requests that resolve to private, loopback, or metadata endpoints.</p>
                <p>Every connector enforces allowlists, rate limits, and request size limits so test traffic cannot be used to pivot into internal networks.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row g-4 mt-3">
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <h3 class="h6 text-uppercase">Data retention</h3>
                <p>Test payloads are stored only for the retention window you configure. You can purge runs on demand, export records, or set automated deletion schedules.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <h3 class="h6 text-uppercase">Audit trail</h3>
                <p>Every action is logged with actor, timestamp, and environment context. Audit logs are immutable and exportable for compliance reporting.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <h3 class="h6 text-uppercase">Responsible disclosure</h3>
                <p>We welcome security reports via our disclosure program and acknowledge findings within one business day. Verified issues receive remediation timelines and status updates.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="cta-section text-white py-5">
    <div class="container text-center">
        <h2 class="fw-bold">Need a security review?</h2>
        <p class="lead">Our team can share documentation, security posture summaries, and custom data residency details.</p>
        <a class="btn btn-light btn-lg" href="/contact">Contact security</a>
    </div>
</section>
